It can contain lists, lists of pending tasks, the calendar, the music library and other personal and professional tools.
It is as if Google Drive, Microsoft Outlook, Slack and Spotify are all available in one browser and at the same time.
One thing that is unique to online data storage is that the user is the one who decides completely who can access what type of information.
The company calls this 'personal data training'.
The idea behind Inrupt, according to the company &apos; s CEO, John Bruce, is to embed the resources, processes and skills necessary for Solid to reach everyone.
